President Biden has declared a major disaster in the State of New York and authorized Federal aid to assist in recovery efforts following the remnants of Hurricane Ida. The declaration makes Federal funding available to affected individuals and governments in certain counties. Assistance may include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to help individuals and business owners recover. Federal funding is also available for emergency work, facility repair or replacement, and hazard mitigation measures. Lai Sun Yee has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing, and additional assistance may be designated in the future. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance online or by phone. Further information can be obtained from the FEMA News Desk.